Equation 1: 5x - 6y = -42  
Equation 2: -4x + 6y = 36  

We can solve this system using algebraic methods. Adding the two equations eliminates y:
(5x - 6y) + (-4x + 6y) = -42 + 36  
→ (5x - 4x) + (-6y + 6y) = -6  
→ x = -6  

Now substitute x = -6 into one equation to find y. Using Equation 1:  
5(-6) - 6y = -42  
→ -30 - 6y = -42  
→ -6y = -12
